summary: An ordinance to the City of Seattle, amending Section 2 of Ordinance No. 44710 of said City, entitled "An Ordinance of the City of Seattle granted to the Great Northern Railway Company, its successors and assigns, the right, privilege and authority to lay down, construct, maintain and operate sundry railway tracks along and across Atlantic Street and Sixth Avenue South in said city, and granting to said company, its successors and assigns, rights of way for such tracks along and across said street and avenue."
